docs.lead_paragraph: KENNEY--James Joseph, beloved father, husband, friend, and longtime editor of photography at Newsweek magazine, died Friday, December 6th in Charleston, South Carolina at the age of 81, after a prolonged illness. He is survived by daughters Elizabeth, Theresa, and Patricia; predeceased by his beloved wife Frances and son James. He was born in Manhattan on March 19, 1932 to Delia and Andrew Kenney. He attended the Power Memorial Academy High School and graduated from Iona College in 1954. He worked for the Associated Press before beginning his distinguished career at Newsweek, where he dedicated himself to advancing the magazine's award-winning photojournalism. Jim was a sharp-witted conversationalist with a wide variety of interests; he loved nature and the outdoors, and was an avid golfer and fan of the Mets and football Giants. He will be deeply missed by colleagues and friends, who fondly remember his laughter, warmth, and easygoing manner. His loved ones invite remembrances to be posted at Legacy.com.
